      "raw": "Adding a duration to a start time: \\\\[ t_{end} \\;=\\; t_{start} \\;+\\; \\Delta t \\\\] Where the duration is the sum of components: \\\\[ \\Delta t \\;=\\; d\\cdot 86{,}400{,}000 \\;+\\; h\\cdot 3{,}600{,}000 \\;+\\; m\\cdot 60{,}000 \\;+\\; s\\cdot 1{,}000 \\;+\\; \\mathrm{ms}\\quad (\\text{milliseconds}) \\\\] Duration between two timestamps: \\\\[ \\Delta t \\;=\\; |\\, t_{end} - t_{start} \\,| \\\\] Splitting a duration into \\\\(n\\\\) equal timers: \\\\[ \\Delta t_i \\;=\\; \\frac{\\Delta t}{n}\\quad \\text{for } i=1,\\dots,n \\\\]"
    }
